As we end 2022, I can’t help but think how this was without a doubt my favorite year EVER. So I wanted to take time and give credit to the amazing vendors and companies who made our wedding a dream day! This also goes without saying that I’m forever grateful for all of our wonderful friends and family who took time out of their lives to celebrate Mike and I this year ❤️

A few things:
I will forever advocate to invest in good photographers as that’s something you’ll have for forever! 

We still get compliments on how awesome our DJ was- and I can confirm he was AMAZING!

Oak Hills Country Club is our home away from home. The staff who work their have become great friends, and they made our day so special. I’m so glad we could celebrate our day with them. 

Last, the wedding process can be stressful. I made sure to work with quality vendors, where I could trust their creative process and minds to make beautiful pieces for our wedding.

Okay one more thing. Mid-way through wedding planning is when sh*t hit the fan. Some may remember, but I wanted to cancel the wedding and elope just us two. Thankfully Mike reminded me this was our wedding, and no one else’s. It was also at that time I realized “you can only control what you can control.” I started saying this out loud, and shockingly it worked to help ease any stress and anxiety I was feeling. It’s something I continue to do/say even after the wedding- and it totally helps saying it out loud to yourself 😊
2022 you were the most amazing, wonderful, magical, fun, life-changing year 🫶🏻✨❤️

4 months down ❤️ Find you someone who dips and twirls you 🫶🏻

✨WE’RE BACK ✨ After a scary and stressful summer, I’m back on my workout shizzzzz 💪🏻

Most of you know the ins and outs of what happened this summer. And I’d do it all again to be there for my family & take care of my husband. 

But the workouts took a back seat. I wasn’t eating good & was drinking lots of wine. 

I was in fight or flight mode for a month plus, and all those emotions I wasn’t allowing myself to feel in the moment caught up with me last week. 

I realized I was missing my daily workouts. That me-time to jam out to music. That daily endorphin high. So I promised myself after Labor Day we were getting back to it- and here we are. IT FELT SO GOOD!

Taking it one day at a time, but I can’t wait to see where I’m at this time next year 🩷

Tips for mums👇🏻

3. Avoid watering the blooms, and focus watering at the base/soil of your mums
